author: The Road to Wembley (FA Cup Finals 1923 - 2000)
text:
Remembering the late great former #Everton, #Arsenal & #England player Alan Ball who sadly passed away OTD in 2007 aged just 61.

Ball played in 2 #FACup finals, losing on both occasions. First in 1968 for Everton and then in 1972 for Arsenal. 

#EFC #AFC

@FootballArchive https://t.co/VfMrRLyQDo

text: @FACupWembley @FootballArchive The 1934 #FACup Final is the only one to date to involve two future knights

author: The Road to Wembley (FA Cup Finals 1923 - 2000)
text:
Remembering the late Sir Stanley Rous who was born OTD in 1895.

Rous, a regular figure at the #FACup final, often seen in the Royal Box, was also a steward at the very first Wembley FA cup final in 1923 & also refereed the 1934 final.  

He died in 1986 aged 91.
@FootballArchive https://t.co/TFwKkh4mIf
